&lt;p&gt;Datadog is seeking an Associate Event Marketing Manager to join our high-performing team and support third-party events and tradeshows across the North America and Latin America regions. As a key member of Datadog’s Event Marketing team – the driving force behind our high-impact, experiential marketing programs – you will play a critical role in executing best-in-class events that generate leads, pipeline, and scale our brand presence. With hundreds of events run globally each year, this role requires someone who is highly organized, detail-oriented, and thrives in a fast-paced environment. The ideal candidate has a proven track record of delivering high-quality event experiences, consistently meeting deadlines, and collaborating cross-functionally. If you’re passionate about creating impactful brand experiences and excited to help shape Datadog’s event footprint, we’d love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Datadog, we place value in our office culture - the relationships and collaboration it builds and the creativity it brings to the table. We operate as a hybrid workplace to ensure our Datadogs can create a work-life harmony that best fits them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute Datadog’s presence at sponsored events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and enact tradeshow promotional plans intended to maximize company exposure and produce sales leads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Captain our events by managing event logistics from conception to completion – staffing, booth space, schedules, pre and post event promotion, and ensuring lead goals are met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and track event budgets, expenses, KPIs, and ROI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain client and sponsor relationships while managing external communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and negotiate various service provider and event contracts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross functionally with teams to ensure events are on brand, on message, and attracting the right audience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of event management experience, executing lead generating events, in a high-tech, fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to identify trends, troubleshoot, escalate, track, and resolve issues by strategically thinking and balancing a broad range of internal and external factors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable of managing both time and event budgets effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to handle high-stress situations calmly and professionally while juggling a variety of projects and deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team-oriented with a sense of optimism&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift up to 25 lbs and stand on feet for extended periods of time during the event.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing to travel up to 50% (both domestic/international) and work a flexible schedule as needed (evenings/weekends)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Datadog values people from all walks of life. We understand not everyone will meet all the above qualifications on day one. That&#39;s okay. If you’re passionate about technology and want to grow your skills, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits and Growth:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous and competitive benefits package&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New hire stock equity (RSUs) and employee stock purchase plan&lt;/li&gt;
